title: Many errors thrown when running testscript.py immediately after installation, output not matching tutorial

labels.name: howtousedlc
labels.description: issue regarding the use of DeepLabCut

body:
** System Information **
OS: MacOS 10.15.17
DeepLabCut Version: Latest version, downloaded today (20 July 2021)
Anaconda env used: DEEPLABCUT (from DEEPLABCUT.yaml)


**Problem Description**
Direct reference to my recent response to #1413 (reposting as a separate issue because #1413 was closed). When I run testscript.py, as described in the tutorial video (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IOWtKn3l33s) immediately after installing DLC and then activating the conda environment, the execution of the program seems to throw multiple exceptions and errors which do not appear in the video. A lot of the data and messages about training the network also do not appear for me. Not sure why. 

**Screenshots**
![Screenshot 2021-07-20 at 4 23 15 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37655744/126407757-66c9a5bc-47a6-401c-9a3e-ebc600cf2b54.png)
![Screenshot 2021-07-20 at 4 22 40 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37655744/126407759-660d7766-d3ae-4219-90fe-849bd01ca57b.png)

**Additional context**
Also had some interesting, potential "error", messages thrown during the installation of the conda environment from the .yaml file (i.e. when executing conda env create -f DEEPLABCUT.yaml). Not sure if this is relevant. Screenshot below:

![Screenshot 2021-07-20 at 4 06 03 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37655744/126407837-08213651-01e5-4dac-a6db-4233d746d035.png)
